.TH "rproc_coredump_add_custom_segment" 9 "rproc_coredump_add_custom_segment" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
rproc_coredump_add_custom_segment \- add custom coredump segment
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" rproc_coredump_add_custom_segment
.BI "(struct rproc *rproc "  ","
.BI "dma_addr_t da "  ","
.BI "size_t size "  ","
.BI "void (*dumpfn)(struct rproc *rproc, struct rproc_dump_segment *segment, void *dest, size_t offset, size_t size) "  ","
.BI "void *priv "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "rproc" 12
handle of a remote processor
.IP "da" 12
device address
.IP "size" 12
size of segment
.IP "dumpfn" 12
custom dump function called for each segment during coredump
.IP "priv" 12
private data
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Add device memory to the list of segments to be included in the coredump
and associate the segment with the given custom dump function and private
data.
.SH "RETURN"
0 on success, negative errno on error.
